Serves 2–3
Total time: ~70 minutes (mostly passive)

⸻

Ingredients

Potatoes
	•	4 medium starchy potatoes (Russet / Maris Piper / King Edward)

Confit Phase
	•	Neutral oil (canola or rice bran), enough to fully submerge
	•	30 g unsalted butter (or vegan butter)
	•	2 cloves garlic, lightly smashed
	•	1 sprig rosemary or thyme

Seasoning (Post-Confit)
	•	1 tsp fine sea salt
	•	1 tsp smoked paprika
	•	½ tsp garlic powder
	•	½ tsp onion powder
	•	½ tsp black pepper
	•	Optional: pinch MSG

Finish
	•	20 g melted butter
	•	Fresh parsley or chives
	•	Optional: lemon zest or parmesan / nutritional yeast

⸻

Method

1. Shape the Potatoes
	•	Peel potatoes.
	•	Trim all sides to form clean rectangular blocks.
	•	Slice lengthwise into 2.5–3 cm slabs.

Uniform geometry matters. Irregular shapes fail.

⸻

2. Accordion Cuts
	•	Place slab between two chopsticks.
	•	Slice vertically every 3–4 mm, stopping at the sticks.
	•	Rotate slab 90°.
	•	Slice diagonally at the same spacing.

Do not rush. Clean cuts = separation later.

⸻

3. Oil Confit (Core Technique)
	•	Place potatoes in a small oven-safe pot or deep tray.
	•	Add garlic, herbs, butter.
	•	Cover fully with neutral oil.
	•	Oven at 150°C (300°F) for 40–45 minutes.

Potatoes must be fully tender with zero browning.

This step replaces boiling and fixes dryness permanently.

⸻

4. Drain & Chill (Mandatory)
	•	Carefully remove potatoes.
	•	Drain on rack or towel.
	•	Chill uncovered in fridge 30–60 minutes
(or freezer 15 minutes).

Cold starch + hot oven = maximal crisping.

⸻

5. Season
	•	Mix all seasoning ingredients.
	•	Sprinkle evenly over potatoes.
	•	Brush lightly with melted butter.

Do not add spices earlier. They burn.

⸻

6. Blast Roast
	•	Oven 245°C fan (475°F)
	•	Place potatoes cut-side up on parchment.
	•	Roast 15 minutes
	•	Flip carefully.
	•	Roast another 12–15 minutes

Edges should be deep golden and audibly crisp.

⸻

7. Finish & Serve
	•	Brush with remaining butter.
	•	Garnish with herbs.
	•	Optional zest or cheese.
	•	Serve immediately.
